shared_text:
Rogers ISD
May 29 at 2:18 PM ·

Merk Field is ready for Graduation tonight at 8:30. Gates will open at 7:30 for invited guests. Here are a couple of reminders:
1. If you have symptoms, stay home and watch on Facebook Live (we will go live at 8:15)
2. Please wear a face mask as a sign of respect to others
3. If you will be sitting on the field, bring your chair. (Wagons will be allowed to transport chairs)
4. You MUST enter with your entire group. If you are sitting on the field, enter through visitor’s side gate, if sitting in the bleachers, enter on home side.
5. Please practice social distancing while entering, during the ceremony, and exiting the stadium
6. REMEMBER: we have done our best to make this event memorable for our Seniors. Much of this was pulled together in the past 10 days. It may not be perfect, but we have tried our best.

W.A.R.

shared_text:
Nash Fares‎Rogers Eagle Football
September 12, 2018 at 6:50 PM ·

We are having a special fundraiser to support Coach Roten and his family as they are at Texas Children’s Hospital in Houston with sweet Annalee. She sailed through her surgery like a champ on Monday but she will have a long recovery ahead of her that will require continued hospitalization. We would like to show our support as the Rogers Eagles family and community to help offset some of the financial burden in the months ahead of them. We will have Down Syndrome Awareness silicone bracelets available on Friday to wear proudly to show our love and support for this precious baby and her family. If you would like to purchase one please see one of the coaches, Mrs. Bertha Harris, or a school administrator. They will also be available for purchase in the school offices, administration building, and Fieldhouse. The bracelets will be $3 each, but any additional donations are welcome! ........... They will soar like wings on Eagles. Isaiah 40:31. #WAR

MS volleyball 7A and 8A play in the Rockdale tournament this Saturday. All MS teams play Monday, 10/9, at Franklin beginning at 5pm. They will play in two gyms.

Football teams are off this week, except for MS. MS teams will play on Thursday at Mart. District action starts Thurs, Oct 12th with the JV at home vs. Comfort at 6pm, and the MS teams travel to Comfort beginning at 5pm. The varsity game is at Comfort on Friday, Oct 13th to open district play.

Cross Country district meets are coming up with the MS teams competing Saturday, Oct 7th at Jarrell and the HS teams also at Jarrell on Monday, Oct 9th.

Rogers ISD
August 16, 2017 at 3:54 PM ·

In an effort to celebrate the positive things going on at Rogers ISD, we want to brag on our teachers and students whose STAAR scores last year were at 90% or at least 10 points above the state average. If you see one of these teachers or students who were in these grades / subjects, tell them "Great Job"

5th Grade Math - 97% (16 pts above state avg)
5th Grade Reading - 90% - (19 pts above state avg)
6th Grade Reading - 83% - (16 pts above state avg)
7th Grade Reading - 85% - (13 pts above state avg)
7th Grade Writing - 79% - (11 pts above state avg)
8th Grade Reading - 88% - (12 pts above state avg)
U.S. History - 96% - (4 pts above state avg)

We had several other grades / subjects VERY close to these goals. We expect many more next year. Keep up the GREAT WORK Teachers & Students. You make Rogers ISD Proud!

Rogers ISD
August 9, 2017 at 3:00 PM ·

In an effort to help our community, the Rogers CYC (community wide Christian Youth Club) group is organizing an event where people can donate any clothes / shoes that your kids have outgrown or don't wear anymore and then we will make these items available to families that may need them. First Baptist Rogers has graciously donated their facility to host the event. Drop off for donated items will be THIS Friday (August 11) from 2:00 - 4:00 pm at the fellowship hall. The items will be for sale ($.25 - $1.00) on Saturday from 8:30 - 11:00 am at the fellowship hall. Any items not sold will be donated to other local organizations. If your kids have outgrown their last year's clothes, they may be able to fit someone else. When Eagles help Eagles.....Everyone wins! The proceeds will help fund the CYC Wednesday after school program, which last year served about 50 kids per week at NO COST to them.

Please share this post so we can get the word out about this event. It's a short turnaround this year, but hopefully we can make it an annual event.

post_text:
The summer is quickly coming to a close and August is rapidly approaching. I am looking forward to another wonderful year of Cross Country and working with your children. Next week I will be at school on Monday through Thursday (July 24th-27th) at 7:00 AM. This will not be a mandatory CC practice but, I hope that if you are in town you will encourage your child to attend. An early start will help all of the runners get there legs under them before they start football/volleyball. The first official week of practice will be Monday July 31st through August 4th at 6:30 AM. If you have any questions or need anything, let me know.

Thanks,

Coach Jarrett

On Saturday October 15th (tomorrow), we'll be producing the annual Haunted House at the RISD Fall Carnival; admission will be $3 a person and will be held in the '41 Hallway of the High School.

On Sunday October 16th, we will be presenting our fall production, A Midsummer Night's Dream at 4:30 PM on the stage of the Carol Ann Bonds building. Admission will be $3 for students and $5 for adults.

Proceeds from both will help fund theatre activities throughout the year. As always, we appreciate your support!

Thursday was a great night for the Eagles!
7th grade football beat Johnson City 16-6. 8th grade won 35-0, and the JV was victorious, 38-16.

Also 8A volleyball beat Franklin in 2 sets. If you have other volleyball scores, please comment.
